The stress in each rod is  

\[
\sigma = \frac{(L_{\text{brass}}\alpha_{\text{brass}}+L_{\text{steel}}\alpha_{\text{steel}})\,\Delta T}
{L_{\text{brass}}/E_{\text{brass}}+L_{\text{steel}}/E_{\text{steel}}}
= \frac{0.042\ \text{cm}}{5.0\times10^{-11}\ \text{cm}^3/\text{dyne}}
= 0.84\times10^{9}\ \text{dyne/cm}^2 .
\]

Thus the correct choice is **J**.  

**the answer is (J)**

To obtain the \(z\)-parameters we invert the admittance matrix:

\[
Y=\begin{bmatrix} y_{11} & y_{12}\\ y_{21} & y_{22}\end{bmatrix}
   =\begin{bmatrix}0.25 & -0.05\\ -0.05 & 0.10\end{bmatrix}\; \text{mho}
\]

Determinant  

\[
\Delta = y_{11}y_{22}-y_{12}y_{21}=0.25(0.10)-(-0.05)(-0.05)=0.025-0.0025=0.0225
\]

Inverse (the \(Z\)-matrix):

\[
Z = Y^{-1}= \frac{1}{\Delta}
\begin{bmatrix}
y_{22} & -y_{12}\\
-y_{21} & y_{11}
\end{bmatrix}
= \frac{1}{0.0225}
\begin{bmatrix}
0.10 & 0.05\\
0.05 & 0.25
\end{bmatrix}
\]

\[
\frac{1}{0.0225}=44.44\;\text{(approximately)}
\]

Thus  

\[
\begin{aligned}
z_{11} &= 44.44 \times 0.10 \approx 4.44\;\Omega,\\
z_{12} &= z_{21}= 44.44 \times 0.05 \approx 2.22\;\Omega,\\
z_{22} &= 44.44 \times 0.25 \approx 11.1\;\Omega.
\end{aligned}
\]

These values correspond to option **A**.

**The answer is (A).**

